   <body>
      <context>
         <p>By connecting an optional portable audio device to the AUX input jack (stereo mini jack) on the unit and then simply selecting the source, you can listen on your car speakers.</p>
         <fig>
            <image href="media/image506a.png" placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Turn the VOLUME dial left to decrease the volume level.</p>
            <p>
               <p>The AUX volume can also be controlled separately through the connected device.</p>
               <fig>
                  <image href="media/image561a.png" placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Turn the external audio equipment off Open the cover, connect
the audio output of the external audio equipment to AUX input
terminal on the unit.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Turn the external audio equipment on. Start playback of the external audio
        equipment at a moderate volume. </p>
            <p>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_i2d_pss_5gc">
                     <image href="media/image554.png" id="image_l2d_pss_5gc" placement="inline"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Press the AUX button to select the AUX function.
        </p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <image href="media/image617a.png" placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Set your usual listening volume by turn the VOLUME dial left/right on the
          unit.</p>
            <p>
               <p>Once the connector is disconnected, the previous mode will be restored.</p>
               <p>AUX
          mode can be used only when an external audio player has been connected.</p>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
